x4freetext: CROSS SECTIONS OF OXYGEN BETWEEN 6 AND 15 MEV.
OF 3 - 13 MEV DEUTERON BEAMS WITH 1 NS PULSES AT A
REPETITION RATE OF 1 MHZ. PTB NEUTRON SCATTERING
DEUTERIUM GAS TARGET CELL OF 3 CM LENGTH, FILLED
FIVE NE213 LIQUID SCINTILLATION DETECTORS, FOUR
HAVING THE DIMENSIONS 25.4 CM DIAMETER BY 5.1 CM THICK
AND ONE 10.2 CM DIAMETER BY 2.54 CM THICK. PLACED
IN A MASSIVE COLLIMATOR SYSTEM CONSISTING OF POLY-
ETHYLENE, WATER AND CONCRETE. NEUTRON-GAMMA DISCRIMI-
NATION TECHNIQUES EMPLOYED. DETECTOR GAIN STABILITY
WITHIN 0.5 PERCENT. THE THRESHOLD OF 500 KEV ELECTRON
LOS ALAMOS-TYPE PROTON RECOIL TELESCOPE USED
.THE SAMPLES WERE PLACED 17.5 CM FROM THE TARGET. THE
.WATER, ENCLOSED IN AN ALUMINUM CAN WITH 0.2 MM WALL
FOR BACKGROUND SUBTRACTION THE FOLLOWING SAMPLES WERE
IN ADDITION, A POLYETHYLENE SAMPLE WAS USED TO CHECK

OF 5 CM, THE CHEMICAL PURITIES WERE HIGHER THAN 99.5
.THE DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR MULTIPLE SCATTERING,
FLUENCE ATTENUATION IN THE SAMPLE AND FINITE GEOMETRY
EFFECTS USING THE MONTE-CARLO CODE STREUER.
